			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-4">
					<div id="ctl00_MainContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_RichHtmlField2_label" style='display:none'></div><div id="ctl00_MainContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_RichHtmlField2__ControlWrapper_OregonRichHtmlField" class="ms-rtestate-field" style="display:inline" ></div>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-4">
					<div id="ctl00_MainContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_RichHtmlField3_label" style='display:none'></div><div id="ctl00_MainContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_RichHtmlField3__ControlWrapper_OregonRichHtmlField" class="ms-rtestate-field" style="display:inline" ></div>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-4">
					<div id="ctl00_MainContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_RichHtmlField4_label" style='display:none'></div><div id="ctl00_MainContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_RichHtmlField4__ControlWrapper_OregonRichHtmlField" class="ms-rtestate-field" style="display:inline" ></div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-sm-6">
					<div id="ctl00_MainContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_RichHtmlField5_label" style='display:none'></div><div id="ctl00_MainContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_RichHtmlField5__ControlWrapper_OregonRichHtmlField" class="ms-rtestate-field" style="display:inline" ></div>
				</div>
				<div class="col-sm-6">
					<div id="ctl00_MainContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_RichHtmlField6_label" style='display:none'></div><div id="ctl00_MainContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_RichHtmlField6__ControlWrapper_OregonRichHtmlField" class="ms-rtestate-field" style="display:inline" ></div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-12">
					<div id="ctl00_MainContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_RichHtmlField11_label" style='display:none'></div><div id="ctl00_MainContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_RichHtmlField11__ControlWrapper_OregonRichHtmlField" class="ms-rtestate-field" style="display:inline" ><h2 class="ms-rteElement-Heading2">Contracting with OPRD</h2><p>If you are interested in being considered for contracts with the Oregon Parks and Recreation Department, please fill out the&#160;form below and&#160;share your business information with OPRD. To complete this form, you will be required to submit a Certificate of Insurance and W-9 Form.&#160;<br></p><h2 class="ms-rteElement-Heading2"><a href="https&#58;//app.smartsheet.com/b/form/ed15c909f55e495393bd491536b788d9">Vendor Prequalification Form</a><br></h2><p><br></p><div class="ms-rtestate-read ms-rte-wpbox"><div class="ms-rtestate-notify  ms-rtestate-read 93101368-fc44-4fde-a7c9-7c8420a84219" id="div_93101368-fc44-4fde-a7c9-7c8420a84219" unselectable="on"><div id="MSOZoneCell_WebPartWPQ6" class="s4-wpcell-plain ms-webpartzone-cell ms-webpart-cell-vertical ms-fullWidth ">
	<div class="ms-webpart-chrome ms-webpart-chrome-vertical ms-webpart-chrome-fullWidth ">
	<div    id="WebPartWPQ6"  class="ms-WPBody "   style="" ><div id="ctl00_ctl40_g_93101368_fc44_4fde_a7c9_7c8420a84219">
		<div class="list-unstyled panel-group or-accordion-list" id="accordion-ctl00_ctl40_g_93101368_fc44_4fde_a7c9_7c8420a84219_ctl01">
			<div class="panel panel-default or-accordion-panel" id="panel-ea584395-d522-42ba-9d4b-9ae98006953a">
				<h4>
					<button class="collapsed btn btn-link or-accordion-panel-btn" href="#ea584395-d522-42ba-9d4b-9ae98006953a" aria-controls="ea584395-d522-42ba-9d4b-9ae98006953a" data-toggle="collapse" aria-expanded="false"><div class="panel-heading" id="afa9eeca-d83c-4c4d-a1bb-c37052ccfe84">
						<div class="or-accordion-heading">
							<div class="or-accordion-heading-title">
								<p class="panel-title">Small Procurement for Goods, Services, A&amp;E and Related Services, and Construction</p>
							</div><span class="or-accordion-heading-collapse" role="img" aria-hidden="true"></span>
						</div>
					</div></button>
				</h4><div class="panel-collapse collapse" id="ea584395-d522-42ba-9d4b-9ae98006953a" >
					<div class="panel-body">
						<div class="or-accordion-content-field">
							Small Procurement for Goods, Services, A&amp;E and Related Services, and Construction
						</div><div class="or-accordion-content-field">
							<div class="ExternalClassAEC1F509BED04535A3752DFED9DD799C"><p>Small Procurements&#160;for Goods, Services, A&amp;E and Related Services, and Construction project thresholds are $1 to $100,000. These projects will be quoted and awarded in any manner OPRD deems practical or convenient, including by direct selection or award&#160;per OAR 736-146-0012(3).​<br>​<br></p></div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div><div class="panel panel-default or-accordion-panel" id="panel-01b207d9-291e-4795-bec8-201b019ee937">
				<h4>
					<button class="collapsed btn btn-link or-accordion-panel-btn" href="#01b207d9-291e-4795-bec8-201b019ee937" aria-controls="01b207d9-291e-4795-bec8-201b019ee937" data-toggle="collapse" aria-expanded="false"><div class="panel-heading" id="3a4681de-3409-41ca-ac64-6ce225a2f89a">
						<div class="or-accordion-heading">
							<div class="or-accordion-heading-title">
								<p class="panel-title">Intermediate Procurement for Goods, Services, A&amp;E and Related Services, and Construction</p>
							</div><span class="or-accordion-heading-collapse" role="img" aria-hidden="true"></span>
						</div>
					</div></button>
				</h4><div class="panel-collapse collapse" id="01b207d9-291e-4795-bec8-201b019ee937" >
					<div class="panel-body">
						<div class="or-accordion-content-field">
							Intermediate Procurement for Goods, Services, A&amp;E and Related Services, and Construction
						</div><div class="or-accordion-content-field">
							<div class="ExternalClassEE2DE912CB104F6191EEFBE1733160E9">Intermediate Procurements for Goods, Services, A&amp;E and Related Services, and Construction project thresholds are $100,000&#160;to $500,000. These procurements&#160;are required to seek at least three informally solicited competitive price quotes or competitive proposals from prospective contractors&#160;per OAR 736-146-0012(6).​<br>​<br><br></div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div><div class="panel panel-default or-accordion-panel" id="panel-64f55ef7-fb24-40ac-8e5e-4ff8cc161618">
				<h4>
					<button class="collapsed btn btn-link or-accordion-panel-btn" href="#64f55ef7-fb24-40ac-8e5e-4ff8cc161618" aria-controls="64f55ef7-fb24-40ac-8e5e-4ff8cc161618" data-toggle="collapse" aria-expanded="false"><div class="panel-heading" id="1f71d037-7337-4448-b2ca-da7504a9c914">
						<div class="or-accordion-heading">
							<div class="or-accordion-heading-title">
								<p class="panel-title">Formal Procurement for Goods, Services, A&amp;E and Related Services, and Construction</p>
							</div><span class="or-accordion-heading-collapse" role="img" aria-hidden="true"></span>
						</div>
					</div></button>
				</h4><div class="panel-collapse collapse" id="64f55ef7-fb24-40ac-8e5e-4ff8cc161618" >
					<div class="panel-body">
						<div class="or-accordion-content-field">
							Formal Procurement for Goods, Services, A&amp;E and Related Services, and Construction
						</div><div class="or-accordion-content-field">
							<div class="ExternalClass71F13A3ED12C40748C59BB4D3718DDDF"><p>Formal Procurements for Goods, Services, A&amp;E and Related Services, and Construction project thresholds that exceed&#160;$500,000. These projects must be awarded by using a formal Request for Proposal (RFP) process if contractor selection will be based on criteria in addition to cost or if the ability to negotiate terms and conditions with the selected contractor is desired. The solicitation process must provide opportunities for prospective proposers to protest the solicitation and the award&#160;per OAR 736-146-0012(5). All Large Procurements will be posted to Procurement Opportunities tab listed above.​​<br></p></div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div><div class="panel panel-default or-accordion-panel" id="panel-d2096842-87e4-4514-a266-5ead30c046ba">
				<h4>
					<button class="collapsed btn btn-link or-accordion-panel-btn" href="#d2096842-87e4-4514-a266-5ead30c046ba" aria-controls="d2096842-87e4-4514-a266-5ead30c046ba" data-toggle="collapse" aria-expanded="false"><div class="panel-heading" id="7e101df1-917b-419a-a356-c4f355efb864">
						<div class="or-accordion-heading">
							<div class="or-accordion-heading-title">
								<p class="panel-title">Information Technology Procurements</p>
							</div><span class="or-accordion-heading-collapse" role="img" aria-hidden="true"></span>
						</div>
					</div></button>
				</h4><div class="panel-collapse collapse" id="d2096842-87e4-4514-a266-5ead30c046ba" >
					<div class="panel-body">
						<div class="or-accordion-content-field">
							Information Technology Procurements
						</div><div class="or-accordion-content-field">
							<div class="ExternalClass64BD6F8716404592AC035B31BB4DF571"><p>​Information Technology Procurements will be solicited as needed. All procurements will follow existing review&#160;thresholds for Department of Administrative Services Enterprise Information Services and Cybersecurity Services ​as required.<br></p></div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div><div class="panel panel-default or-accordion-panel" id="panel-a9434ffa-823d-478d-84c1-6692de1c828c">
				<h4>
					<button class="collapsed btn btn-link or-accordion-panel-btn" href="#a9434ffa-823d-478d-84c1-6692de1c828c" aria-controls="a9434ffa-823d-478d-84c1-6692de1c828c" data-toggle="collapse" aria-expanded="false"><div class="panel-heading" id="dfc854f3-b270-4c9b-a39a-e068c2a2299d">
						<div class="or-accordion-heading">
							<div class="or-accordion-heading-title">
								<p class="panel-title">Price Agreements</p>
							</div><span class="or-accordion-heading-collapse" role="img" aria-hidden="true"></span>
						</div>
					</div></button>
				</h4><div class="panel-collapse collapse" id="a9434ffa-823d-478d-84c1-6692de1c828c" >
					<div class="panel-body">
						<div class="or-accordion-content-field">
							Price Agreements
						</div><div class="or-accordion-content-field">
							<div class="ExternalClass87F0FFCB896E41FEBAEC092650B0FCD4"><p>​OPRD is no longer required to use mandatory use price agreements. OPRD will use price agreements that are advantageous to the agency based on need, cost, and terms and conditions.&#160;<br></p></div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div><div class="panel panel-default or-accordion-panel" id="panel-ad41dfdf-0eb4-4485-81c1-950713c68fed">
				<h4>
					<button class="collapsed btn btn-link or-accordion-panel-btn" href="#ad41dfdf-0eb4-4485-81c1-950713c68fed" aria-controls="ad41dfdf-0eb4-4485-81c1-950713c68fed" data-toggle="collapse" aria-expanded="false"><div class="panel-heading" id="dc3d04c8-cecf-4a6c-9f39-4c1d8bbdfda8">
						<div class="or-accordion-heading">
							<div class="or-accordion-heading-title">
								<p class="panel-title">Sole Source Procurements</p>
							</div><span class="or-accordion-heading-collapse" role="img" aria-hidden="true"></span>
						</div>
					</div></button>
				</h4><div class="panel-collapse collapse" id="ad41dfdf-0eb4-4485-81c1-950713c68fed" >
					<div class="panel-body">
						<div class="or-accordion-content-field">
							Sole Source Procurements
						</div><div class="or-accordion-content-field">
							<div class="ExternalClass4778DB0DD3B340E0B67B55A726E14EC0"><p>S​ole Source Procurements are procurements&#160;&#160;for goods or services without competition that exceed a 
contract price of $100,000 if OPRD determines in writing that the goods or services are available 
from only one source. OPRD must base sole source determination on written findings that may include&#58;<br><br>(A) That the efficient utilization of existing goods requires acquiring compatible goods or 
services;<br>(B) that the goods or services required to exchange software or data with other public or private 
agencies are available from only one source; <br>(C) that the goods or services are for use in a pilot or an experimental project; or <br>(D) other findings that support the conclusion that the goods or services are available from only 
one source.&#160;</p><p>​OPRD must, to the extent reasonably practical, negotiate with the sole source provider to obtain contract terms that are advantageous to OPRD.<br></p></div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div><div class="ms-clear"></div></div>
</div>
